docs.lead_paragraph: 12:06 a.m. | Updated The Senate clash over the unemployment benefits ended just before midnight Thursday with Senator Jim Bunning, Republican of Kentucky, refusing to lift his objection, meaning the  jobless aid - for however short a time - will run out Sunday night unless a deal is reached Friday.

headline.main: Bunning Blocks Jobless Aid in Senate

docs.lead_paragraph: I'll be writing more about the health care summit over the weekend, but I just want to make one quick point on policy. The big news leading into the event was the Wall Street Journal's report this morning that the White House has prepared a more modest, fallback health reform plan in the event it becomes clear comprehensive reform is going nowhere. Or perhaps I should say the big "news," since Ezra Klein quickly came out with a post saying that nobody in Obamaland is seriously considering the proposal at the moment. (It certainly wasn't mentioned at the summit.)
